    <p> When we arrived in Wellington, we found a parking lot right next to the Te Papa Museum. There we pulled a parking ticket for 24 hours at 10:30 a.m. So we had already found our place for the night and one problem less. </p>
    <p> We went straight to the museum. The museum is just huge. It goes through countless levels that are divided into several subject areas again. Outside there is even a tropical rainforest with a waterfall and reproduced stalactite caves. We only went into the area that showed us how much New Zealand was in the lack of primeval forces such as volcanoes and earthquakes. Then it was about animal life ashore and in the water before we plunged into the culture of the Maori. Currently you can even learn something about the Maori and its meaning in a special exhibition. </p>
    <p> We got hungry slowly. Since the museum is free of charge, we first decided to go back to the cars and make lunch. Then it continued with the culture of the Maori and the settlement history of the western peoples. Even themes such as the problems between the peoples are dealt with there. </p>
