    <p> We walked along a street lined with pubs and restaurants. At the end of this, we found that we run in the wrong direction. So we turned over and found each other again three in the main shopping street. After a round through the streets, we decided to run back to the museum on the water and use the free WiFi and free electricity there to plan the next stages. Before we made our way to our beds, we enjoyed a little walk through the alley with the pubs and restaurants. </p>
    <p> The next morning the alarm clock rang very early, as we had to make our way to the ferry to overlap from the north to the South Island. Everything went smoothly on the ferry when you disregard the small kick -off that we got because we had tickets for small vans and not for motorhomes. However, our cars are not larger than small vans. I don't see it to pay for a large motorhome just because there is a bed on the loading area. </p>
    <p> But as the saying goes: God immediately punishes God. As soon as the ferry stuck out of the harbor, it started to rock quite violently. Since about 50% of the 3.5 hour crossing went over the open sea and Sam became so suspicious, I decided to get such tablets against swinging for both of us. Green faces could be seen everywhere on the way to the shop. I saw a woman coming out of the toilet who was greener on the face than the grass in Ireland. She took 5 steps. Looked around and ran back into the toilet with a handkerchief in front of his mouth. At the sight, I slowly got a little strange and I watched that we both took tablets. After about 30 minutes I got really nice heartburn and so I could choose whether I was sick or swing. </p>
