    <p> Fortunately, we finally drove into the fjord landscape and the swings stopped. After a few maneuvers through narrow islands, we reached Picton. When we left, we found that there was still a little snow on the side of the road. We then made our way to Blenheim, where I wanted to get fresh bread one last time before we drove to the weakly populated west coast. <br> The road from Blenheim to Saint Arnaud goes across a wide level that can be driven more relaxed than the a little north of the SH6 that leads across mountains. The level reminds me a little of the route in front of Sibiu before driving through the Romanian Carpathians. </p>
    <p> When we arrived at the campsite, we made ourselves over 3 parking spaces with our 2 small cars so that nobody could adjust the view and the promised sunshine for the next morning. </p>
